                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-120-off639 t18230409-120-crimeloc642"></join>, a box of raisins stood on a cannister inside my door; I saw them when I opened the shop, about<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182304090048"></xptr>half-past seven o'clock in the morning. We were at breakfast in the back parlour, and saw somebody come in and go out of the shop; I ran and missed the raisins, and saw the prisoner with the box under his arm, about twenty yards off. I followed and took him with them.</p>
               <p>
            
